<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0050793/2026-01-23> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of development, the biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a multicellular organism over time from an initial condition (e.g. a zygote, or a young adult) to a later condition (e.g. a multicellular animal or an aged adult)." ;
