<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0051050/2026-01-23> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore." ;
    evo:isDeprecated false ;
    evo:label "positive regulation of transport" ;
