<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0052041/2026-01-23> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of host programmed cell death, leading to a decrease in the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death in the host cell. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction." ;
    evo:isDeprecated false ;
    evo:label "symbiont-mediated suppression of host programmed cell death" ;
