    evo:definition "A process in which a symbiont gene product affects host apoptosis, leading to a change in the frequency, rate or extent of apoptosis in the host cell. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction." ;
    evo:isDeprecated false ;
    evo:label "symbiont-mediated perturbation of host apoptosis" ;
