<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0061213/2025-10-10> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of mesonephros development. Mesonephros development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the mesonephros over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The mesonephros is an organ that filters the blood and excretes the end products of body metabolism in the form of urine." ;
    evo:isDeprecated false ;
    evo:label "positive regulation of mesonephros development" ;
    evo:termID "GO:0061213" ;
    evo:version <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/version/2025-10-10> .

