    evo:definition "Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of release of cytochrome c from mitochondria, the process in which cytochrome c is enabled to move from the mitochondrial intermembrane space into the cytosol, which is an early step in apoptosis and leads to caspase activation." ;
    evo:isDeprecated false ;
    evo:label "positive regulation of release of cytochrome c from mitochondria" ;
