<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0010656/2025-10-10> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "Any process that decreases the rate or frequency of muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a muscle cell and result in its death." ;
