<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0010657/2025-10-10> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "A form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases, whose actions dismantle a muscle cell and result in its death. A muscle cell is a mature contractile cell, commonly known as a myocyte, that forms one of three kinds of muscle." ;
