<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0010658/2025-10-10> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "A form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases, whose actions dismantle a striated muscle cell and result in its death. Striated muscle cells make up striated muscle fibers which are divided by transverse bands into striations." ;
