<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0033554/2025-10-10> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress. The stress is usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation)." ;
