<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0033668/2025-10-10> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of host apoptosis, leading to a decrease in the frequency, rate or extent of apoptosis in the host cell. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction." ;
