<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0034050/2025-10-10> a evo:TermVersion ;
    evo:definition "Cell death resulting from activation of endogenous cellular processes after interaction with a symbiont (defined as the smaller of two, or more, organisms engaged in symbiosis, a close interaction encompassing mutualism through parasitism). This can be triggered by direct interaction with the organism, for example, contact with penetrating hyphae of a fungus; or an indirect interaction such as symbiont-secreted molecules." ;
    evo:isDeprecated false ;
    evo:label "symbiont-induced defense-related programmed cell death" ;
    evo:parent go:GO_0012501,
        go:GO_0140546 ;
    evo:termID "GO:0034050" ;
    evo:version <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/version/2025-10-10> .

